<sect1 id="sampletracer_page_1sampletracer_intro">
<title>Introduction</title>
<para>The <ref refid="classsampletracer" kindref="compound">sampletracer</ref> class tracks multiple samples (files/directories) and their associated containers. It serves as the top-level organizer for multi-sample analyses.</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="sampletracer_page_1sampletracer_methods">
<title>Methods</title>
<para><table rows="8" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="yes"><para>Method   </para>
</entry><entry thead="yes"><para>Description    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>add_meta_data()</computeroutput>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Add metadata for a file    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>get_meta_data()</computeroutput>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Retrieve metadata    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>add_event()</computeroutput>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Register event template for sample    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>add_graph()</computeroutput>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Register graph template for sample    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>add_selection()</computeroutput>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Register selection    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>compile_objects()</computeroutput>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Process all containers    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>populate_dataloader()</computeroutput>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Transfer all graphs   </para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
</sect1>
